text: Catia Sofía Da Silva Machado, known as Catia Da Silva, is an Andorran footballer who plays as a defender for Andorran-based Spanish Women's First Division of Catalonia club ENFAF and the Andorra women's national team. ==International career== Da Silva made her senior debut for Andorra in November 2018 against Luxembourg. She also capped in a 1–2 friendly loss to the same opponent in June 2019. ==References== Category:Living people Category:Women's association football defenders Category:Andorran women's footballers Category:Andorra women's international footballers Category:Andorran people of Portuguese descent Category:Year of birth missing (living people)
